# Complexity
- Time complexity:
The time complexity of the dynamic programming solution is $$O(mn)$$, where m and n are the lengths of word1 and word2, respectively. This is because we fill up a 2D array of size (m+1) x (n+1) using nested loops.
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
The space complexity of the dynamic programming solution is $$O(mn)$$, where m and n are the lengths of word1 and word2, respectively. This is because we use a 2D array of size (m+1) x (n+1) to store the minimum number of operations required to convert substrings of word1 to substrings of word2.
