solutions.content:
__Recursive Approach__(TLE) : In this Approach for Word1 we have 3 Operations which are Insert, Delete or Replace.

If the First character of both of the Words are same then we need not to perform any of the Operation but if the Character is not same then we need to check which of the Operation among the insert, delete or replace will give the minimum answer.

So to find the minimum answer we need to check all of the 3 Possible Operations and then we will check among them which is minimum and then simply return the answer.

**In Case the Character of both of the Word is Matching**
Simply Skip the similar character and hunt for the dissimilar One in the Word1.

**In Case the Character we are Checking is not matching with the Character of Word1**
1. __Insert__ : In this Case we will Insert in Word1 the same Character as that of the Word2 so that we can make the Word1 to match Word2.
2. __Delete__ : In this Case we will Delete the Character from the Word1 as the character was not matching with the Word2.
3. __Replace__ : We will replace the dissimilar Character of the Word1 with Word2.

Note : After calculating the Minimum of all of the Possible 3 Operations then we need to Add 1 to the answer as We have not included the cost of current Operation. 
For e.g.,
word1 = "horse"
word2 = "ros"

```
                          (horse, ros)
// First Character of both the Words are Different then 3 Operations will be Performed
			      /             |            \
		     (Insert)        (Delete)       (Replace)
			   |                |                |
		(rhorse, ros)       (orse,ros)       (rorse,ros) 
// It is to be noted that the first Character of Word1 will surely become same as that of the Word2. In order to get minimun answer we need to perfrom such Operations Otherwise we will not get the Optimized answer.
               |                |                |  // We can directly write this stage in next Operations
          (horse, os)      (orse, ros)        (orse, os) 
		 /     |     \          .                  |  //Simply Skip the Character
(horse, s) (orse, ros) (orse, s).               (rse, s)
    .           .          .    .                   .
    .           .          .                        .
    .           .          .                        .
	So on.
```
**Base Case** : Base Condition should be if any of the Word is consumed completely then we need to stop working as not we cannot check if the characters are same or not.

In the Base case, 3 Cases are Possible :
1. **Both of the Word are Consumed** : Then ans is zero as the empty Strings are also equal.
2. **Word1 is Consumed** : In this case Word2 is available and now our work is to convert the empty String into the Word1, So we need to perform Insertions Equal to length of the Word2. Hence we can return the Length of the Word2.
3.  **Word2 is Consumed** : In this case Word1 is available and now our work is to convert the this String into the Empty, So we need to perform deletions Equal to length of the Word1. Hence we can return the Length of the Word1.

So we will return Math.max(Word1.length(), Word1.length());
```
public static int helper(String s1, String s2){
		if(s1.length() == 0 || s2.length() == 0){ // If length any of the Length is Consumed completely
			return Math.max(s1.length(), s2.length()); // Discussed Above
		}

		if(s1.charAt(0) == s2.charAt(0)){ // If the Character matches
			return helper(s1.substring(1),s2.substring(1)); // Skip both of the Characters
		}else{
			int insert = helper(s1, s2.substring(1)); // In case of Insertion Consume the S2 character
			int delete = helper(s1.substring(1), s2); // In case of Deletion Consume the S1 character
			int replace = helper(s1.substring(1), s2.substring(1)); // In case of Replace Consume the characters from both of the Strings


			return Math.min(insert, Math.min(delete, replace)) + 1; //Return the minimum Operations among the 3 Operations + 1.
		}
	}
```

**TopDown Approach** : This Approach is Similar as discussed Above but In this Approach we will create and Save the calculated answer in an Array called as Storage.
```
public static int helperTD(String s1, String s2, int[][] strg){
		if(s1.length() == 0 || s2.length() == 0){
			return Math.max(s1.length(), s2.length());
		}
		int n = s1.length();
		int m = s2.length();
		if(strg[n][m] != 0){  //If we have Already Calculated the Answer
			return strg[n][m]; // return the Saved Answer
		}

		if(s1.charAt(0) == s2.charAt(0)){
			strg[n][m] = helperTD(s1.substring(1),s2.substring(1), strg); // Saving Answer
			return strg[n][m];
		}else{
			int insert = helperTD(s1, s2.substring(1), strg);
			int delete = helperTD(s1.substring(1), s2, strg);
			int replace = helperTD(s1.substring(1), s2.substring(1), strg);
			strg[n][m] = Math.min(insert, Math.min(delete, replace)) + 1; // Storing the calculated answer
			return strg[n][m]; // return the Calculated Answer
		}
	}
```

**BottomUp Approach** : 
```
public static int helperBU(String s1, String s2){
		int[][] strg = new int[s1.length() + 1][s2.length() + 1];
		for(int i = s1.length();i >= 0;i--){
			for(int j = s2.length();j >= 0;j--){
				if(i == s1.length()){
					strg[i][j] = s2.length() - j;
					continue;
				}
				if(j == s2.length()){
					strg[i][j] = s1.length() - i;
					continue;
				}
				if(s1.charAt(i) == s2.charAt(j)){
					strg[i][j] = strg[i + 1][j + 1];
				}else{
					int insert = strg[i][j + 1];
					int delete = strg[i + 1][j];
					int replace = strg[i + 1][j + 1];
					strg[i][j] = Math.min(insert, Math.min(delete, replace)) + 1;
				}
			}
		}
		return strg[0][0];
	}
```

