solutions.content:
## For any DP question there are 2 parts: 
1) Base case: Always think of what the smallest possible input could be. In our case, lengths of string word1 and word2 (let M = length of word1 & N = length of word2).
So, base case is if(M==0 || N==0). 
If M==0, we simply insert all n characters of word2 into it and return N.
If N==0, we simply delete all m characters in word2 and return M.
Basically we return Max(M,N). If both are 0, it returns 0.

2) Choice tree
Let's say at an instant we have the first m characters of word1 and the first n characters of word2. How do we solve the question for this instance? ```minDist(word1, word2, m, n)  ```
Our strategy is to keep on reducing the input step-by-step and check the last characters of both the inputs. For the last characters, we have 2 possibilities.
* Both characters are same ( word1.charAt(m) == word2.charAt(n) )
We don't need any operation because both characters are same.
Simply reduce the input length and return ```minDist(word1, word2, m-1, n-1) ```
* Characters are different  ( word1.charAt(m-1) != word2.charAt(n-1) )
Now we have 3 possibilities:
	1.  Insert the character word2.charAt(n) after the current index 'm' of word1 
	Since we inserted a new character in word1 to match word2.charAt(n). keep m same and reduce n by 1. ```return 1 + minDist(word1, word2, m, n-1)``` (1 is the cost of the insertion operation).
	2.  Delete the character word1.charAt(m). 
	Since we deleted a character from word1 because it didn't match with word2.charAt(n).
	Decrease m by 1 and keep n the same. ```return 1 + minDist(word1, word2, m-1, n)``` (1 is the cost of the deletion operation). 
	3.  Substitute the character word1.charAt(m) with word2.charAt(n). Decrease m and n both by 1. ```return 1 + minDist(word1, word2, m-1, n-1)``` (1 is the cost of the substitution operation). 

	Now, simply take the minimum of what these 3 possibilities and return it as the answer for this instance of the function call ```minDist(word1, word2, m, n)```
	Then just use a 2D matrix(dp) to store the solution for memoization.
	Time complexity: O(MN)
```
	public int minDist(String x, String y, int m, int n, int dp[][]){
        if(m==0 || n==0)
            return Math.max(m,n);
        if(x.charAt(m-1)==y.charAt(n-1))
            return minDist(x,y,m-1,n-1, dp);

        if(dp[m][n-1]==-1) dp[m][n-1] = 1+minDist(x, y, m, n-1, dp);
        if(dp[m-1][n]==-1) dp[m-1][n] = 1+minDist(x, y, m-1, n, dp);
        if(dp[m-1][n-1]==-1) dp[m-1][n-1] = 1+minDist(x, y, m-1, n-1, dp);

        return dp[m][n] = Math.min(Math.min(dp[m-1][n-1],dp[m-1][n]), dp[m][n-1]);

    }
    public int minDistance(String word1, String word2) {
        int m=word1.length(), n=word2.length();
        int t[][]=new int[m+1][n+1];
        for(int i=0;i<=m;i++)
            for(int j=0;j<=n;j++)
                t[i][j]=-1;
        return minDist(word1, word2, m, n, t);
    }
